images.caption: Virginia House Speaker M. Kirkland Cox (R-Colonial Heights) has announced the creation of a select committee on school safety.
European model shows storm well southeast of Washington on Monday morning, far enough for the storm to completely miss.
The NAM model shows precipitation from the Sunday-Monday Mid-Atlantic storm remaining south and southeast of Washington.
American (GFS) model shows the D.C. area on the northern edge of snow from a coastal storm Monday morning.

Snowfall forecasts from the group of simulations in the American (GEFS) modeling system. Note that these accumulations assume 10 inches of snow would fall for every inch of rain, whereas it would, in reality, be less given the wet nature of snow that falls.
The UKMet forecast created Wednesday for Monday in the Mid-Atlantic showed a big storm coming up the East Coast. Thursday’s forecast has a much weaker storm headed out to sea.
